    <item>
      <title>Alternative Localization</title>
      <author>SimpsonGames</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/545846</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/545846#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">7e04df7359e594baac4e77961376098e09debe23</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 09 Oct 2024 21:14:53 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6702f85f98711.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66fc51012cc1a.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66fc510bd57b2.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66fc5105d94a3.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66fc5103ed4e7.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66fc5103f1722.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66fc510a1a576.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66fc510ca2173.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66fc510d6791e.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66fc510db6008.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66fc510dac311.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66fc510ccf825.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66fc510d248e1.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66fc510d288f9.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66fc510d6daa6.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66fc510d8f6df.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; Modular Version Release Update&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Addition&lt;/em&gt;: Renamed Minister Lefte to Minister Sadari&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Addition&lt;/em&gt;: Renamed General Wright to General Ugi&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Adjustment&lt;/em&gt;: Renamed Mod Folder to "Alternative Localization"&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Addition&lt;/em&gt;: This update also sees the release of the new Modular Version! Included are different modules that you can pick and choose to your liking! Be sure to read the README!&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;[NOTE: This mod is NOT supposed to be a "more accurate translation" of Echoes of Wisdom's English localization. It is simply a for-fun mod that provides a new localization for the game by changing some things around!]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod changes a bunch of names and terms in the game; this could either be names seen in previous games in the series, or terms that aim to make some names more interesting.&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Changed Names&lt;/h2&gt;Examples of names and terms this mod changes are:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Suthorn → Ordon&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Jabul Waters → Zorana Waters&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Oasis → Kara Kara Oasis&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Seesyde Village → Lurelin Village&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Hyrule Ranch → Lon Lon Ranch&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Eternal Forest → Lost Woods&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lord Jabu-Jabu's Den → Lord Jabu-Jabu's Cavern&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lueburry → Robbie&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Deku Tree → Great Deku Tree&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Strandula → Skulltula&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Crawltula → Skullwalltula&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sanctions → Blessings&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Prime Energy → Triforce&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Descriptive Prefixes&lt;/h2&gt;This mod also replaces the "Lv." suffix used by some items and echoes to descriptive words instead to make them a little more interesting. Examples include:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Darknut Lv. 2 → Strong Darknut&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Deku Baba Lv. 2 → Big Deku Baba&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Tangler Lv. 2 → Angler Tangler&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Gibdo Lv. 2 → Ancient Gibdo&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lizalfos Lv. 3 → Mighty Lizalfos&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sword of Might Lv.2 → Tempered Sword of Might&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sword of Might Lv. 3 → Master Sword of Might&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Learned Echo Formatting&lt;/h2&gt;This mod also changes the formatting of the "you learned the X echo!" dialogue to be better formatted and less like it's using an internal file name. For example:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Before: "You learned the Hyrule-castle-pot echo!"&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;After: "You learned the Hyrule Castle Pot echo!"&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Modular Version&lt;/h2&gt;Included as a separate download, the modular version of this mod splits the original&amp;nbsp;into individual parts so you can pick and choose which changes you'd like!&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Included with the download is a text file detailing every single option you can choose from, so make sure to read it! All of the modules are organised into individual folders so picking out the options you'd like should be easy! The modular version contains:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Modules (Locations, Enemies + Items, Characters, Misc)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Groups&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="SelectedElement"&gt;Extra (Bonus Game Over text changes)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;Due to the way this mod is put together, several changes edit the same files. This can cause conflicts and result in some changes not being shown. To try to avoid this, some changes have been grouped together such as location names, character names, etc.&amp;nbsp;Hopefully, this issue can be completely negated in the future with a mod manager that can merge MSBT files, though this will most likely not be a thing for a long while.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As an added bonus, I've included some extra options that edits the "Game Over" text to more&amp;nbsp;humorous options! Feel free to try them!&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod affects the English localization only (US and EU). As this is a big mod, there's a chance I might've missed something. If there are any misspellings, formatting problems, or any other issues, let me know and I'll fix them as soon as I can!&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/alternative-localization-full-v103_9bcbf.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/alternative-localization-modular-v103.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/relocalization-full-v102.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/relocalization-full-v101.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/relocalization-full.zip" type="application/zip"/>
